{
  "info": {
    "name": "OTP Email Verification - API Endpoints",
    "description": "Email OTP Verification endpoints for user registration",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000/api",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "test_email",
      "value": "testuser@example.com",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "OTP Email Verification",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Send OTP Code",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{test_email}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/send-otp/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "send-otp", ""]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Verify OTP Code",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{test_email}}\",\n  \"otp_code\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/verify-otp/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "verify-otp", ""]
            }
          },
          "description": "Replace 123456 with the actual OTP code sent to your email"
        },
        {
          "name": "3. Resend OTP Code",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{test_email}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/resend-otp/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "resend-otp", ""]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "4. Register with OTP (Complete Registration)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"johndoe\",\n  \"email\": \"{{test_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\",\n  \"password_confirm\": \"SecurePass123!\",\n  \"first_name\": \"John\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Doe\",\n  \"otp_code\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/register-with-otp/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "register-with-otp", ""]
            }
          },
          "description": "Complete registration after verifying OTP. Make sure OTP is verified first!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Usage Instructions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "OTP Registration Flow",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": [""]
            }
          },
          "description": "STEP-BY-STEP REGISTRATION FLOW:\n\n1. SEND OTP:\n   - Call endpoint '1. Send OTP Code'\n   - Provide your email in the test_email variable\n   - You should receive an OTP in your email (or console if using console backend)\n\n2. VERIFY OTP:\n   - Call endpoint '2. Verify OTP Code'\n   - Copy the OTP from your email\n   - Replace '123456' with the actual OTP\n   - Email must match the one from step 1\n\n3. REGISTER WITH OTP:\n   - Call endpoint '4. Register with OTP'\n   - Fill in username, password, name fields\n   - Use same email from step 1\n   - Use same OTP code from step 2\n   - If successful, you'll get JWT tokens\n\n4. USE TOKENS:\n   - Copy the 'token' value from response\n   - Use it in Authorization header: Bearer <token>\n   - Now you can access authenticated endpoints\n\nNOTE: OTP expires after 10 minutes. If it expires, start from step 1 again."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
